# AddressRAG Dataset Schema and Data Dictionary

Version: 1.0.0  

Repository: https://github.com/lx7-127/AddressRAG

## 1. Scope and Availability

This document describes the structure of the toponym-address corpus used in the AddressRAG experiments. The experimental corpus contains 3,000 records, with one toponym-address or point-of-interest (POI) record per row.

The source records were obtained from Amap and remain subject to the applicable data license and terms of use. Therefore, this release does not contain raw place names, administrative names, detailed addresses, coordinates, platform identifiers, source records, or other traceable values. Only the schema, field definitions, aggregate completeness counts, controlled-value definitions, and anonymization rules are provided.

The authors should specify a separate license for this documentation and the released code. That license does not supersede the terms applicable to the original Amap data.

## 2. Dataset-Level Schema

| Property | Definition |
|---|---|
| Logical dataset name | `toponym_address_corpus` |
| Unit of observation | One selected toponym-address or POI record |
| Primary key | `sample_id` |
| Experimental record count | 3,000 |
| Number of fields | 21 |
| Geographic design | Two-city cross-city corpus; public artifacts use `CITY_A` and `CITY_B` |
| Sampling design | Deterministic stratified sampling by city code and source POI category |
| Source POI strata | `catering_service`, `scenic_spot`, `public_facility`, `life_service` |
| Coordinate reference system | WGS84 geographic coordinates (`EPSG:4326`) |
| Coordinate unit | Decimal degrees |
| Text encoding | UTF-8 when exported to a text-based format |
| Sampling seed | `20260608` |
| STA generation | Deterministic rule- and template-based transformation, not free-form LLM generation |
| Public release | Schema and documentation only; licensed record-level values are not redistributed |

## 3. Field Groups

| Field group | Fields | Source class | Main role | Public treatment |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Record identity | `sample_id` | Derived | Stable join key for sampling and evaluation | Release a newly generated public ID |
| Toponym and address | `place_name`, `province`, `city`, `district`, `detailed_address` | Licensed source or parsed | Entity identity and administrative containment | Replace with stable pseudonyms |
| Spatial coordinates | `longitude`, `latitude` | Licensed source | Spatial attributes and coordinate questions | Remove or redact |
| POI classification | `poi_type`, `category_level_1` to `category_level_5` | Licensed source plus deterministic parsing | Classification mapping and KG attributes | Release only coarse public classes or pseudonymous codes |
| Task annotations | `administrative_granularity`, `query_difficulty`, `sampling_stratum` | Deterministic derived | Stratification and subgroup analysis | Release normalized codes |
| Semantic augmentation | `semantic_text` | Deterministic derived | STA output used for KG construction | Regenerate from anonymized fields |
| Provenance | `source_file`, `source_sheet` | Ingestion metadata | Internal audit trail | Replace with generic source codes or remove |
| Reproducibility | `selected_random_seed` | Fixed parameter | Deterministic sampling | Release unchanged |

