## 5. Controlled Values for Public Artifacts

### 5.1 Source POI Category

| Code | Definition |
|---|---|
| `catering_service` | Catering and food-service source stratum |
| `scenic_spot` | Scenic attraction source stratum |
| `public_facility` | Public-facility source stratum |
| `life_service` | Daily-life service source stratum |

### 5.2 Administrative Granularity

| Code | Definition |
|---|---|
| `building_or_house_number` | Building, unit, or house-number level |
| `road_or_street` | Road or street level |
| `district_or_general_poi` | District/county or general-POI level |
| `poi_internal_point` | Internal point within a POI or scenic site |
| `township_or_community` | Township, subdistrict, or community level |

### 5.3 Query Difficulty

| Code | Definition |
|---|---|
| `standard_address_retrieval` | Direct lookup from a sufficiently specified address |
| `ambiguous_or_same_name` | Query involving a duplicate, alias, or ambiguous toponym |
| `incomplete_or_nonstandard_expression` | Incomplete, colloquial, or non-standard address description |
| `spatial_reasoning_query` | Query requiring multiple attributes or administrative/spatial reasoning |

## 6. Anonymization Rules

| Field group | Required action | Consistency requirement |
|---|---|---|
| Record identifiers | Create new public IDs. Do not expose or directly hash source-platform identifiers. | IDs must be unique and stable across released files. |
| Toponyms | Replace real place names with stable POI codes such as `POI_A`. | Use the same code in the question, context, answer, and KG artifact. |
| Administrative names | Replace real names with hierarchical codes such as `PROV_A`, `CITY_A`, and `DIST_A`. | Preserve the containment chain, for example `PROV_A > CITY_A > DIST_A`. |
| Detailed addresses | Replace with `ADDRESS_A`-style placeholders or null. | Questions and reference answers must use the same placeholder. |
| Coordinates | Remove and represent as null or `[REDACTED]`. | Omit or rewrite coordinate questions unless synthetic coordinates are explicitly identified as synthetic. |
| POI taxonomy | Retain only coarse categories or replace detailed labels with codes. | Maintain the same category mapping across QA and KG artifacts. |
| Derived annotations | Release normalized codes. | Recompute `sampling_stratum` after pseudonymizing city values. |
| STA narrative | Regenerate from anonymized structured fields using the original deterministic templates. | Manually verify question-context-answer consistency. |
| Provenance | Replace file and worksheet names with generic source codes or remove them. | Codes must not encode real city or category names. |
| Random seed | Release unchanged. | Verify that the documented seed matches the released sampling pseudocode or script. |

